modules.description: This module provides functions to generate and manipulate 2D triangular meshes from planar straight-line graphs (PSLGs), supporting mesh creation, reading, and writing in EasyMesh file formats. It works with geometric data structures such as points, segments, holes, and regions, and allows specifying markers and constraints for mesh refinement. Concrete use cases include generating finite element meshes for numerical simulations, reading and writing mesh data for visualization or processing, and defining complex 2D domains with boundaries and holes for computational geometry tasks.
